## Limitations

The findings are based on available literature and may not encompass all perspectives on anti-science attitudes. The complexity of the issue means that individual cases may vary significantly, and the generalizations made here might not apply universally. Additionally, the rapidly changing political and social landscapes can influence these attitudes, necessitating ongoing research and adaptation of strategies to address them.